text: Akhtubinka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Khosheutovsky Selsoviet, Kharabalinsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 417 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Ashuluk River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kharabalinsky District
title: Akhtubinka
